{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CrhGzdXJqa7fPHtsk3PC3e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are applied and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**Changes applied to all 3 members:**\n\n| Setting | Before | After | Method |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `logLevel` | 1 | **2** | Runtime `setParameter` + persisted in `mongod.conf` |\n| `slowOpThresholdMs` | 200 ms | **400 ms** | Runtime `setProfilingLevel` + persisted in `mongod.conf` |\n| WiredTiger journal compressor | snappy | **zlib** | Persisted in `mongod.conf`, applied via rolling restart |\n\n**How it was done:**\n1. Applied `logLevel=2` and `slowms=400` immediately via `setParameter`/`setProfilingLevel` on all running members (no restart needed).\n2. Created a `mongodb-config` ConfigMap with `/etc/mongod/mongod.conf` containing all three settings.\n3. Patched the StatefulSet to mount the ConfigMap and pass `--config=/etc/mongod/mongod.conf` to `mongod`.\n4. The StatefulSet rolling update restarted pods one-at-a-time (secondaries first, then primary stepped down naturally), keeping data available throughout.\n\nReplica set is healthy: 2 secondaries + 1 primary, all `health=1`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":367,"cache_read_input_tokens":45109,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":367},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8262fe2d-d18d-4f60-8fa8-693499bf1782","uuid":"350cadba-6e09-4226-a38a-9eb36a2ac130","request_id":"req_011CcgGpyXtgFJejJNAhg5TE"}
